Remed respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. To give the best experience, Remed collects your personal information such as Name, Email address, contact information, user-generated content, and user data usage. 

Remed also uses tracking technologies to collects your device information, such as type, browser type and version, IP address, operating system, and data about your browsing and usage patterns on our app.

Data collected will be used to personalize and tailor our services to your preferences and interests. With your consent, we will send you updates, newsletters, and promotional materials, analyze user behavior, improve our services, and protect our services and users 
from unauthorized access and fraudulent activity.

We do not sell your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your data with any service providers. However, we may engage third-party service providers to assist us in delivering our services, such as hosting, analytics, and marketing.

We may disclose your information in response to a legal request or when required to comply with applicable laws. We may retain your data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy unless a more extended retention period is required or 
permitted by law.

You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you and request corrections. You may also request inaccurate or incomplete data about you, the deletion of your personal information, subject to legal obligations, object to processing your 
data for marketing purposes, or a copy of your data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format.

We employ industry-standard security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. We may update this policy to reflect changes in our data practices. We will notify you of any material changes.

If you have any questions or concerns about this policy or your data, please contact us at Teamremedllc@gmail.com

By using our services, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and consent to the collection and use of your data as described herein.
